, evidence, history and contemporary debate. Fully updated, it contains: • a new foreword by Professor Kate Pickett, acclaimed co-author of The Spirit Level • two new chapters on disability and chronic illness, and UK education policy respectively • updated examples and data, reflecting changes in black and minority ethnic demographics in the UK • a post-script from a minority student on her struggle to make a new home in Britain Suitable for undergraduate and postgraduate courses in social policy, sociology and applied social sciences, its global themes of immigration, austerity and securitisation also make it of considerable interest to policy and welfare practitioners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMinoritiesxServices forzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aAtkin, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkin, Karl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeider, Harris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerghs, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBécares, Laia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChattoo, Sangeeta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChattoo, Sangeeta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCole, Bankole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCraig, Gary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDyson, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Ronny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Ronny, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocab